column3:
ACK https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/1ae5839ff024096c65e1590084f2720fa08d3e23

Super-micro-nit: in-place renaming the file make the list of includes non-sorted. The new name should be moved down in the include list. But I understand why it is done this way.

> Super-micro-nit: in-place renaming the file make the list of includes non-sorted.

We've given up on include sorting a long time ago.
Yes, but it is de-facto standard and almost every new code follows it. But as I said, it is super-micro(not tm) nit.\n
